CHAT.comment: Freeplay. Mother and Child sit on living+room floor playing with a box of experimenter provided toys. They first play with a tea set then they play with a small truck with shapes that fit in holes in the top and sides. Child speaks in one word sentences. He uses "Mom" frequently for a variety of purposes. His words are fairly intelligible.

u.a: hands Mother a plate from tea set .
gives cover to teapot to Child .
tries to put top on cup .
points to each plate when he talks .
refers to small box containing tea set .
shakes head no , goes to big box of toys .
can't get shapes out of truck .
picks up new piece , tries to put it in .
tries to put piece in the top of truck .
touches holes on side of truck .
